  "texts": [
    "Besides their recurrent formulation, discrete state space models can be formulated as a convolution with the same set of parameters.",
    "It can be demonstrated that, by \"unrolling\" the linear recurrence (Eq.",
    "(1)), the output sequence y can be obtained via a learnable convolution over the input sequence u:",
    "where K is the convolution filter, parameterized via A, B, and C (see Supplementary Eqs.",
    "(1)-(4) for a detailed derivation)."
  ],
